    <item>
      <title>Rogue definition.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&amp;message.id=4871#M4871</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So there is a long standing debate about Rogue utility versus pure raw Rogue DPS. I wish we would get more utility, but why can't we stick to our class roles at the same time? Why oh why don't we get more &lt;EM&gt;DPS&lt;/EM&gt; utility? We don't have to become Berserkers or song-less Bards. Maybe a&amp;nbsp;discipline like the Monk&amp;nbsp;Dragon Fang&amp;nbsp;disc&amp;nbsp;that costs a bit of endurance that distracts an NPC so that you can get off a guaranteed full damage backstab from any angle with a reuse time greater than at least 1 backstab. So on the encounters where you can't be behind a mob,&amp;nbsp;we aren't as useless. You could make it usable if the Rogue isn't on the top of the hate list (raids that make positioning impossible). Plus, we're Assassins, we should get a discipline where for a short period of time we focus&amp;nbsp;our efforts&amp;nbsp;and point out weaknesses in opponents and in their armor, giving&amp;nbsp;us extra strikethrough and higher critical hit damage on normal and special attacks or something. That's what Assassins do, they kill people, they should be better at it... Maybe a medium damage&amp;nbsp;DoT backstab discipline, or AAs that give a chance for a Gift of Mana type buff proc on backstabs making your next backstab indefinitely critically hit. I'm tired of playing a class that has neither utility or the&amp;nbsp;raw DPS a pure specialization class should have. I'd go with anything really right now... Maybe I'm going the wrong way with the Rogue class, but at the very least I think most of us can agree something needs to be done.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
